To him Toby paid a visit that very evening, down into his den, and walked about, as much as to say “ Come on, Macduff !” but Macduff did not come on, ’ and henceforward there was an armed neutrality, and they merely stiffened up and made their backs rigid, pretended each not to see the other, walking solemnly round, as is the manner of dogS. Toby worked his new-found faculty thoroughly, but with discretion. He killed cats, astonished beggarS, kept his own in his own garden against all comers, and came off victorious in several well-fought battles3 but he was not quarrelsome or foolhardy. It was very odd how his carriage changed, holding his head up, and how much pleasanter he was at horne. To my father, next to William, who was his Humane Society man, he remained stanch. He had a great dislike to all things abnormal, as the phrase now is. A young lady of his acquaintance was calling one day, and, relating some distressing events, she be- came hysterical.
